column4: mallardjewellers.com Maiden Hurdle (Novices' Championship Hurdle Series Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Act Of Innocence,  Ambiente Friendly, 5/1 Gaelic Pride,  Hold The Serve, 9/1 Bras d'Or,  Soldier Reeves, 10/1 Khafre, 12/1 Touch The Moon, 16/1 The Egyptian Ginge, 20/1 Bespoke Tailor, 25/1 Astelia, 33/1 Stay In The Game, 66/1 Portetta, 100/1 Directly,  Keno Black, 150/1 Ribba Hill
column36: Solid bumper record; received a positive review from new trainer in Stable Tour last month
column37: Solid bumper record for Gearoid O'Loughlin then Paul Nicholls, making the frame in two notable races (including on soft ground) prior to taking advantage of drop in class at Taunton (2m, good); received a positive review from new trainer Nicky Henderson in Stable Tour last month; still with same owners; major player.

column4: mallardjewellers.com Maiden Hurdle (Novices' Championship Hurdle Series Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Act Of Innocence,  Ambiente Friendly, 5/1 Gaelic Pride,  Hold The Serve, 9/1 Bras d'Or,  Soldier Reeves, 10/1 Khafre, 12/1 Touch The Moon, 16/1 The Egyptian Ginge, 20/1 Bespoke Tailor, 25/1 Astelia, 33/1 Stay In The Game, 66/1 Portetta, 100/1 Directly,  Keno Black, 150/1 Ribba Hill
column27: Al Shira'Aa Farms S A R L
column36: Best Flat form when placed in the Derby and Irish Derby last year; has schooled well
column37: Had wind surgery since last run and a hood returns; has become disappointing on the Flat but best form under that code, namely placed efforts in the Derby and Irish Derby last year, indicates that he has the potential to become a very classy hurdler; has schooled well; respected; best Flat form on good to soft/good.

column37: Ran well in spring bumpers on good/good to soft; not disgraced on the figures, despite finishing last of five, when the rank outsider in 4yo hurdle over C&D (good) on reappearance; opposed in this competitive field, however.

column4: mallardjewellers.com Maiden Hurdle (Novices' Championship Hurdle Series Qualifier) (GBB Race)

column37: Close second, clear of remainder, at Navan (2m, yielding) on stable/hurdles debut; failed to build on that effort when beaten favourite at Limerick since but Flat form (fairly useful) suggests he should still do better in this sphere; not written off; unraced on soft/heavy.

column36: Consistent over hurdles until form dipped sharply last time; quite exposed
column37: Irish mare who was proving consistent over hurdles, finishing runner-up four times, until form dipped sharply last time; still seeking first success of any description and is quite exposed.

column37: Predictably struggled in Cheltenham Grade 2 on last month's stable/hurdle debut and may have been flattered by her proximity when fourth of five at Ascot (1m7f, good) a fortnight ago; others look stronger.

column36: Irish filly who faces a stiff task on form
column37: Irish filly who is a five-race maiden; placed twice (bumper/hurdle) in the spring; outstayed over 2m6f most recently but faces a stiff task in this field back down in distance.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Bled from nose latest (July); unproven over this far and his chase form needs improvement
column37: Smart hurdler in his prime and a dual chase winner for Henry de Bromhead this spring (2m, yielding/good); reportedly bled from the nose when not discredited at Stratford in July on second start for new yard (off since); acts on soft but unproven over this far and chase form needs improvement.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Did well as novice hurdler; encouraging chase debut; different going on this h'cap debut
column37: Front-runner who did well as a novice hurdler last season (over about 2m4f on good or good to soft) and the last of his three wins was at Cheltenham; made an encouraging chase debut at Uttoxeter 16 days ago behind an odds-on favourite; different ground (he was second in a soft-ground bumper) asks the big question on this handicap debut, but he's on the shortlist.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Sixth in Grade 1 Albert Bartlett novice hurdle here (3m) in March; promising chase recruit
column37: His Irish point win was on heavy going; won at Ffos Las (2m4f, soft) last November on hurdle/rules debut and best form when he belied his huge odds with sixth in the Grade 1 Albert Bartlett Novices' here (3m) in March, having held every chance turning for home; trainer reports that this 6yo goes very well fresh and is a great jumper.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Left H Derham for £75,000; better is needed on handicap debut but he should make a chaser
column37: Irish point and heavy-ground bumper winner; tailed off in Grade 1 at Punchestown festival in May but useful otherwise as a novice hurdler at this sort of trip, albeit coming up well short when 5-4 favourite for a Chepstow Grade 2 five weeks ago; left Harry Derham for £75,000 two weeks later; some improvement is needed on this handicap debut but he should make a chaser.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Asserted after final fence in a six-runner novice handicap on chase debut at Aintree (2m)
column37: Won an Irish maiden point on soft; two wins and two seconds from four starts under rules, on latest start warming to his jumping task before asserting after the final fence in a six-runner novice handicap on seasonal/chase debut at Aintree (2m, good); up 6lb but lightly raced and promising, worth this second attempt at 2m4f.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: 2-16 in chases; hurdle wins on soft and heavy but top ratings have been on better ground
column37: Far and away the most experienced of these, having appeared in 16 chases; won a Tramore beginners' event in August and a Listowel handicap in September, both over 2m6f; below form in another quite valuable on latest outing; it's also a possible concern that although he won over hurdles on soft and heavy, his top ratings have been registered on better ground.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column32: R A Bartlett/J Carthy/Mrs Paul Shanahan
column36: Ex-French 5yo; may have been let in lightly for this handicap on stable debut
column37: Half-brother to three French jumps winners, two pretty useful; dam French 12.5f Flat and 2m-2m3f hurdle/chase winner, half-sister to French 2m3f Grade 1 hurdle winner; all ten races have been in France for Daniela Mele, winning two over hurdles (one on heavy) and one of his three chases; best form when second in Listed handicap at Dieppe (2m6f, soft) in June last time and it's possible that he's been let in lightly for this handicap on stable debut.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl
column36: Favourite for C&D novice handicap last month but badly hampered four out, fell three out
column37: Won last season in a point, an Ascot bumper and Catterick maiden hurdle; beaten 26l in 2m4f Grade 2 novice hurdle here on soft ground, albeit appearing to run creditably facing stiff task; while novice handicap chase over C&D last month (badly hampered off pace four out, fell three out) isn't the race to judge him on and he started favourite that day, it clearly wasn't the ideal chase debut.

column4: Bottlegreen Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Jig's Forge, 7/2 Jax Junior, 4/1 Jordans Cross, 5/1 Kim Roque, 7/1 Queensbury Boy, 10/1 Kdeux Saint Fray, 16/1 Aspire Tower, 20/1 El Champo, 40/1 Rockstown Girl

column36: Ex-Willie Mullins; pulled up on stable debut here last month following an absence
column37: 8yo who is on a handy mark on his best form for Willie Mullins but he was pulled up at 40-1 on his stable debut here last month following an absence and 14,000gns sale; probably best watched.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: Two wins last season and faced tough task here on last month's reappearance; not ruled out
column37: Soundly beaten on last month's reappearance here but faced a tough task from out of the weights and may have needed the run; runs off his proper mark today and he won twice last season (2m, soft); not ruled out.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column27: S C E A Haras De Gratte Panche Et Al
column36: Hampered two out when fifth at Down Royal on second stable start; could be a contender
column37: Won for the late Edward O'Grady at Tipperary (2m, good to yielding) in May and not beaten far when fifth at Down Royal (2m, good to yielding) recently on his second start for this stable, when hampered two out; could be a contender if conditions suit (there's a question mark regarding testing ground).

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: Below best last term but dropped down weights; won this in 2023; could have a part to play
column37: 9yo who wasn't at his best last season but dropped down the weights and showed spark when runner-up at Kempton (2m4f, soft) on his penultimate outing; won this in 2023 (good to soft) and could have a part to play on his reappearance; the tongue-tie adopted on his last two starts is now left off.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)

column27: S A S I E I & Percy Holding Aps

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: 1-1 over fences in France; has joined respected Irish yard; has potential off opening mark
column37: Lightly raced 5yo who won on his chase debut in France (2m3f, heavy) in March, beating a solid yardstick into second; has joined a respected Irish stable and has potential off his opening mark.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: Back to some form with close 3rd at Aintree last Saturday; in the mix if backing that up
column37: Ex-Willie Mullins 9yo who returned to some form in first-time tongue-tie/cheekpieces (both retained) with close third at 28-1 at Aintree (2m, good to soft) last Saturday; also effective on testing ground; in the mix if backing up that latest performance.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: Hampered early when below par at Wexford latest; in good heart previously; one to consider
column37: Below par at Wexford three weeks ago but was badly hampered by a faller at the first fence; in good heart previously, winning at Wexford (2m3f, good) in August and third at Listowel (2m3f, yielding to soft) in September; has won on soft ground; he's one to consider.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: 9yo who staged a renaissance in the spring and there could still be mileage in his mark
column37: 9yo who staged a renaissance in the spring, winning at Newbury (2m, good) then Chepstow (2m, good); there could still be mileage in his mark judged on the promise shown earlier in his career and he's been versatile ground-wise in the past; respected on his reappearance.

column4: Hine Solicitors Talking Sense Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Ballybreeze, 11/2 Battle Of Ridgeway, 6/1 Klass Langy,  Cabhfuilfungi, 13/2 Torneo, 7/1 St Faz,  Triple Trade,  Glengouly, 16/1 Dr T J Eckleburg, 33/1 Uncle Phil,  Calgary Tiger
column36: In good form at end of 2024 but absent since and 11lb out of the handicap today
column37: Ran well when third twice in a row at the end of 2024 but this 10yo has been absent since and is 11lb out of the handicap today.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column32: Sir A Ferguson, G Mason, L Hales, The Late J Hales
column36: Each-way player despite all his races since March 2024 having been at about 2m4f or 2m6f
column37: Triple Grade 1 winner and while all his races since March 2024 have been at about 2m4f or 2m6f, he did win a Betfair Chase at Haydock (extended 3m1f, soft) in 2022 and ran three solid races (two of them in the Gold Cup) over about 3m2f at Cheltenham in 2022 or 2023; each-way player.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column36: Less consistent last term; not dismissed despite others having mostly much younger legs
column37: Less consistent last term than the season before but still won a quite valuable veterans' handicap at Newbury (3m2f, soft) in March under claimer Chad Bament; reappearance in that campaign was another of his better efforts and he used to have a good record on heavy going, so he's not dismissed despite most of the others having much younger legs.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column36: No stamina or ground worries and hacked up first time out last term; this track is a worry
column37: Jumped and hung badly right in the Midlands National at Uttoxeter (4m2f, heavy) in March 2024 but nevertheless battled back to win, and that's the clear highlight among eight chases going this way round; scoring by 31l at Ascot (3m5f, good; 10lb higher today) was a good way to start last season, which he ended tailed off in the Grand National, but the return to Cheltenham (where he ran twice in 2023) is a nagging concern.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column27: S A R L Genetique Obstacle
column36: Huge turnaround is needed; return to mud and blinkers (from cheekpieces) are the big hopes
column37: Won 2023 Welsh National by 34l on heavy (2lb higher today); failed to shine in the Gold Cup or Grand National later in that campaign, before pulled up on both starts last season and again on recent reappearance, albeit with those last three races coming on good ground; a huge turnaround is therefore needed, with return to the mud and blinkers (from cheekpieces) the big hopes.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column36: Goes well on the 3m5f Cross-Country course here; has had a wind operation (his third)
column37: Goes well on the 3m5f Cross-Country course at Cheltenham, on which he was third last December and second at the Festival in March; acts on soft, well beaten sole start on heavy; tailed off on final start last term and has since had a wind operation (his third); also tongue tied first time; the big problem is that a career best is probably needed, at the age of 12.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column27: G Codre & Mrs A & K Kepa
column32: DL Adams, JA Adams & G McPherson
column36: Newcastle third last November showed he stays 2m7f; far more for him to prove at this trip
column37: Went close five weeks ago in a 2m Flat race; seen far more often over jumps and he's 3-10 as a chaser, with a soft-ground Cheltenham second on New Year's Day being one of his best efforts last season but that was over 2m4f; Newcastle third last November showed he stays 2m7f but there's far more for him to prove at this trip.

column4: Oddschecker Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Protektorat, 7/2 Tanganyika, 9/2 Beauport, 8/1 Marble Sands, 10/1 Sam Brown,  Nassalam,  Transmission, 12/1 Latenightpass, 16/1 Lady Balko, 25/1 Fascile Mode
column27: E A L Haras De Montaigu Et Al
column36: Midlands National 2nd; heavy ground no problem; assuming he returns on song, lots to like
column37: Last season's switch to chasing yielded two 3m wins and he ended the campaign with a tenacious second over 4m2f in the Midlands National at Uttoxeter (6lb higher today); all three of those runs were on good to soft but the last two of his hurdle wins were on heavy (latest by 25l in a canter); assuming that this 7yo returns on song, there's a lot to like.

column4: Bar One Racing Troytown Handicap Chase (Grade 3)

column36: Fine effort in first-time cheekpieces when third in the Munster National, definite chance
column37: Progressive handicap hurdler before starting over fences with a win at Kilbeggan (2m4f, good) in June; lost chance at Killarney in July with a bad mistake at the sixth; snug winner of a 2m2f contest at Galway on handicap chase debut; made mistakes in a conditions race at Listowel; fine effort in first-time cheekpieces when third in the Munster National; definite chance.

column37: Very experienced handicap chaser who has been generally reliable over the past 12 months; improved his strike rate (now 5-40 over fences) by winning two handicaps at Kilbeggan during the summer; best at around 2m4f.

column4: Bar One Racing Troytown Handicap Chase (Grade 3)
